-- ANZ Bank May Initiate A$1 Billion Hybrid Issue For KEB Stake, Review Says
-- B y   B e n   S h a r p l e s
-- 2010-11-10T20:23:17Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-10/anz-bank-may-initiate-a-1-billion-hybrid-issue-for-keb-stake-review-says.html
Australia & New Zealand Banking
Group Ltd. is planning a hybrid capital issue of about A$1
billion, the Australian Financial Review reported in its Street
Talk column, without saying where it got the information. The
proceeds may be put towards the potential purchase of a A$4
billion-plus stake in Korea Exchange Bank, the newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ben Sharples in Melbourne at 
